{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require all public toilets to include a baby changing facility for everyone",
        "additional_details": "I want Parliament to debate the lack of accessible changing facilities in men's and unisex toilets to promote gender equality and support parents. Current arrangements often leave fathers unable to care for their children in public spaces, causing inconvenience and unnecessary stress. Ensuring inclusive facilities benefits families, encourages shared caregiving, and promotes a fair, accessible environment for all parents and children.",
        "background": "All public toilets must include a baby changing facility for everyone, ensuring men can easily care for their babies too. This is essential for equality and convenience, and should be mandatory in all public establishments that provide toilet facilities.",
